+## 2026-06-20 (claude/branch-status-check-84t7dh) — audit + fixes: 3 adversarial auditors over the contact-import diff
+
+- **Audited the whole contact-import diff against code** (3 parallel adversarial reviewers: security, correctness, integration). Verdict: **no BLOCKER/HIGH.** Verified-solid: cross-tenant isolation (service-role phone path scopes every read/write by `user_id`; `makeSupabaseAudienceStore` reads `.eq("user_id")`), token integrity (timing-safe, integrity-before-parse), OAuth state/redirect_uri, and the `inserted`/`updated` disjointness (confirmed `ignoreDuplicates + .select()` → `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING RETURNING` at postgrest-js 2.106.1).
+- **Fixes applied (6):** (A) `UploadForm` Google return now gates the "pickable audience" banner on real `/sync` `res.ok` (was flipping success in `.finally()` even on a 500). (B) `prepareContacts` clamps `name` to 200 chars — closes the unbounded-name write on the token-authed phone path (covers every path). (C) QR/import token TTL 10→5 min + honest doc on the within-TTL replay window (single-use deferred to a claim table). (D) QR generated at 176px to match its 176px render. (E) `parse-vcard` strips a `mailto:` scheme so iCloud exports don't store `mailto:x@y.com` (hard-bounce). (F) `emailDomain` strips a trailing dot so `gmail.com.` can't evade the work-email filter.
+- **Gates:** tsc 0, eslint clean, `next build` ✓ Compiled + ✓ TypeScript (env-gated `/charts` prerender only), **407 email tests** (+3 regression: name-clamp, mailto, trailing-dot) / 0 fail. Pushed to `claude/branch-status-check-84t7dh`.
+
 ## 2026-06-20 (main) — feat(contacts): phone + CSV/vCard contact import + work-email filter (Google sign-in first)
 
 - **Context:** "get contacts + emails onto the site, build for phone and csv." Probing remote `main` (this container was a stale shallow clone — fast-forwarded 621 commits to `02a9bac` first) showed the **CSV path already ships** (`email_contacts` + `/api/email/contacts/upload` + `/sync` + `/contacts/upload` UI). So this build is the **missing phone import + work-email filter**, extending the existing pipeline — operator chose **Google sign-in first**, then Android QR, then vCard-accept.
